The University of Tampa’s globally connected campus is the beating heart of a vibrant urban oasis.
The University of Tampa recognizes outstanding individuals and student organizations at its annual Leadership Awards Night.
The University of Tampa is surrounded by beautiful natural resources; resources we tap into to help our students develop the capacity to be transformational leaders in today’s world.
30 freshmen are selected each year as the President’s Leadership Fellows to refine and expand their capacity to lead in a global society through participation in a four-year scholarship program.

Student Accessibility and Academic Support

Designed for students who want to further develop their current leadership skills and competencies, the interdisciplinary <b>Minor in Leadership Studies</b> combines theory and practice; students learn about leadership and then experience it.
The University invites all interested first-year and transfer students to apply for an exciting leadership program: Discover UT.

President's Cabinet
The President’s Cabinet is composed of the University’s senior leadership team, working together to guide and implement the strategic vision of the institution. Together, they advise the president on critical decisions, coordinate University-wide initiatives, and ensure alignment across academic, administrative and service areas.

The mission of the Office of Administration and Finance is one of service, support, and management of institutional resources in a broad array of administrative functions. The responsibilities of this office include:
Financial Accounting and Reporting
Payroll
Accounts Payable
Bursar (Accounts Receivable/Billing)
Purchasing
Investment Management
Risk Management
Legal Affairs
Facilities Management
Facilities Rental
Dining Services
Budget Management
Financial Planning and Forecasting
New Construction and Renovations
Long Term Debt Issuance and Management
Capital Planning
University Store (Barnes and Noble)
